{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"certifiable":true,"findings":[{"citations":[{"description":"test_recorded_channel_survives_compaction only asserts creation_channel == 'python'; no cli/mcp/jira/import variants exist in this file","kind":"file","line_end":100,"line_start":88,"path":"tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py"}],"criterion":"Compacting tickets recorded as cli, mcp, python, jira, and import writes the exact channel into SNAPSHOT.data.compiled_state, retires the source CREATE, and SNAPSHOT-only replay returns the same value without an inference marker. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py -k recorded.","detail":"The single test matched by `-k recorded` — `test_recorded_channel_survives_compaction` — only seeds a ticket via `rebar.create_ticket` (which uses the `python` channel) and asserts `creation_channel == \"python\"`. The four other channels required by AC1 — `cli`, `mcp`, `jira`, and `import` — are never compacted and verified in this test file. There is no parametrized or additional `*recorded*` test that exercises those channels through the compaction→SNAPSHOT→replay cycle, so the stated proof is incomplete for four of the five channels.","dimension":"completion","remediation":"Add parametrized (or separate) `*recorded*` test cases in `tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_creation_channel_compaction.py` that create tickets via the `cli`, `mcp`, `jira`, and `import` ingresses (or seed synthetic CREATE events with those channel values), compact them, and assert the exact channel survives in `SNAPSHOT.data.compiled_state` and in SNAPSHOT-only replay without an inference marker.","reviewer_id":"completion-verifier","severity":"high"}],"material_fingerprint":null,"model":"anthropic:claude-sonnet-4-6","remediation":"How to resolve the unmet criteria: for each one, decide whether the work is genuinely incomplete or simply undocumented. If a requirement is already satisfied but the proof is not discoverable from the code alone, add a comment to this ticket that documents the evidence — cite the concrete artifacts that meet the requirement (file paths and line ranges, commands and their output, links, or the reasoning that ties the work to the criterion). The completion verifier reads this ticket's comments, so evidence you record there is taken into account on the next verification. For any criterion whose work is genuinely unfinished, complete it, then re-verify.","runner":"pydantic_ai","schema":"completion_verifier_fail_v1","ticket_id":"568c-b44b-7e2b-4d87","verdict":"FAIL"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMPLETION_VERDICT","timestamp":1784289815294098001,"uuid":"698b2cbb-dee5-42a3-8eef-6bcb2fda98a3"}